reserves either. It wasn't that much of a problem

34:34.525 --> 34:56.215
if you had gone about it to win it and kept the 
politicians out of it

34:34.525 --> 34:56.215
and let the military get it over with by going after 
the base from which they operated. We didn't do

34:57.818 --> 34:58.559
that. We have got to learn to go fight these wars and 
won in the Middle East without being totally

35:02.605 --> 35:32.410
disruptive to our society and our society on the 
other hand has got to respect this and quit and to

35:02.605 --> 35:32.410
come off of their leftist

35:02.605 --> 35:32.410
disinterest and lackadaisical attitude about 
what is of national interest to the United States

35:33.706 --> 35:41.636
of America and their welfare.

35:44.059 --> 35:45.581
And I don't know when that's going to come.

35:48.845 --> 36:03.223
But we can't be disruptive to the United States 
because we're going to go over and

35:48.845 --> 36:03.223
stop Soviet from taking Saudi Arabia and Kuwait 
and Bahrain and Iraq Israel. We don't need that

36:05.444 --> 36:13.294
much, we don't need total mobilization in this 
country, three years of mobilization and

36:05.444 --> 36:13.294
disruptive of life here.

36:16.037 --> 36:18.600
We need to selectively go about this. What kind of 
progress you make if you take all of the reserve

36:20.483 --> 36:30.275
officers out of the school system here in the 
Dallas-Fort Worth area?

36:30.295 --> 36:32.097
And all the doctors.

36:37.628 --> 36:38.769
and many, many more. Some of the critics have said 
that one of the problems with this war is that we

36:39.550 --> 36:48.457
were trying to win the hearts and minds of the 
people. That was one of the policies. In the South,

36:51.680 --> 36:56.684
yeah, we were using such massive firepower, which 
you've already spoken of. We were using such

36:56.704 --> 37:03.370
massive firepower that we were too dependent on 
technology. Do you think that we were too

37:03.910 --> 37:07.213
dependent on technology? Not at all. First place, 
out where the firepower was being used, there

37:08.830 --> 37:13.535
wasn't any civilians out there. They'd been 
killed off and destroyed 20 years before by a

37:13.575 --> 37:19.962
communist element. And firepower is the cheapest 
way to go. You use firepower instead of expending

37:24.327 --> 37:29.172
American soldiers. American soldiers, he's a 
person. He's people. He belongs to someone

37:32.435 --> 37:34.798
important in the United States. He's important 
himself. You don't want to expend the important

37:36.674 --> 37:45.628
part of America against the cheap part of 
communism. Under communism, people are cheap.

37:50.576 --> 37:55.725
Weapons and materialistic things are very 
important because they're atheist beliefs. But

37:57.127 --> 38:03.357
in American way of life, and in my belief in 
Americans, is that people are important. and that

38:04.248 --> 38:07.691
the cheap part of it, they're made by the grace of 
God. Bombs and artillery pieces and firepower,

38:10.034 --> 38:16.260
that's all made by hand, and that's cheap stuff. 
You can make it in the back end of anybody's garage

38:16.300 --> 38:19.743
in many instances. So why use the important part of 
America, pit the important part of America

38:20.724 --> 38:30.353
against the cheap part of communism? That is the 
American soldier against their soldier. Let's

38:35.416 --> 38:39.400
pit our cheap part of America against the cheap 
part of communism. Let them have the firepower.

38:41.542 --> 38:42.343
That's the way I see it. What did you think of the 
quality of the Vietnamese as far as fighters were

38:43.665 --> 38:48.109
concerned? You mean the South Vietnamese? Yes. 
