38:51.573 --> 39:01.103
and their leaders were getting tired of those that 
hadn't been killed. And after you've been wounded

39:03.057 --> 39:18.780
about 10 times or more in 20 years of war, the 
incentive to go get killed with 11th time is not

39:03.057 --> 39:18.780
very great. And that's a very interesting thing. I 
think that might be true in the case of America

39:20.423 --> 39:25.450
also.

39:26.351 --> 39:30.938
I hope that answered your question on that one. 
good units and there were bad ones, but after

39:32.420 --> 39:40.913
twenty years, you know,

39:32.420 --> 39:40.913
you get pretty tired. Well, the North Vietnamese 
had also been at war for that amount of time, yeah.

39:46.441 --> 39:48.845
They, for the most part, were on the offensive. 
Yep. What did you think of— On the offensive, the

39:49.646 --> 39:56.757
offensive had a—the offensive it's a sort of thing 
that provides adventure and challenge and

39:56.990 --> 40:26.035
there's not much adventure into being on the 
defensive and being kidnapped and clocked and

39:56.990 --> 40:26.035
trying to defend yourself so it's an attitudinal 
sort of thing and in addition to that I have to

39:56.990 --> 40:26.035
compliment the communists

39:56.990 --> 40:26.035
in their products Now, maybe their methods of 
attaining it are not so— are attaining the highest

40:26.875 --> 40:41.254
spree

40:26.875 --> 40:41.254
and the dedication that the communist soldier 
has. I don't—maybe not condone some of their

40:42.796 --> 40:53.030
methods or any of their methods for attaining that 
within an individual, but they do it better than

40:42.796 --> 40:53.030
anybody I know of. You've got to give them credit 
for it. and they make a little guy very tenacious.

41:01.050 --> 41:19.174
But if you've got a person that's

41:01.050 --> 41:19.174
born in the hardship, raised in the hardship,

